|      10.1007/s10207-024-00909-w       | 2024 |      General Purpose      | 4-6 | Yes | S, T, R, I, D, E |         Attack data         |     T2, T3, T5     |          NA           |                                       human subjectivity                                       |                  SCE framework applied to user stories to secure development                   |                                    protect _x000D_cloud-based systems using SCE and Artificial Intelligence_x000D_ when software factories employ DevSecOps practices.                                     |                                       Requires: system cotext as user stories, component list, attack goals, and attack tree root element. Generating this kind of attack-defense tree requires providing the LLM with websites that contain such attacks, e.g., https://cloud.hacktricks.xyz/.                                        |                                                                                                                                                                            Starting from a set of user stories of a certain application, the proposed framework applies LLM to create fine-granularity attack-defense trees in a supervised manner, which in turn serves as input to the SCE component. The latter is applied to a real system to test whether the proposed security controls are effective against identified threats.                                                                                                                                                                            |                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 ChaosXploit (SW), GPTâˆ’3.5 and GPT-4 v (SW).                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 |                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         Demo only: Two SCE experiment are conducted to demonstrate the capabilities of the solution. the first experiment is designed to verify the possibility of detecting the                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          |                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  N/A (No evaluation performed)_x000D_                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  |                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        N/A (No evaluation performed)_x000D_                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        |                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        Pros: it does reduce the time requiredto create realistic threat models based on attack-defense trees.  Cons: existence of possible wrong answers from the LLM. The LLM may not understand the contextof the questions and tend to generate meaningless answers. Cons: there is another limitation regardingthe use of LLMs, which is related to the specific dataset usedfor training because it can introduce different forms of biasin the output. Lesson: it is vital to underline the importance of the consultant (security anallyst)â€™s experience in filtering answers provided to the LLM and provide a proper context. Lesson: ChatGPT-4 could not only inferattacks, but also query websites with attack procedures, which substantially improved the realism of attack-defensetrees. Pros: This proposal constitutes an additional layer of security for the SAST, SCA, and DAST tools, which can be integrated into a CI/CD pipeline_x000D_                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         |          nan           |
