|          10.3390/bdcc7010001          | 2023 |      General Purpose      | 4-6 | No  |       S, T       |        Attack trees         |         NA         |       Empirical       |                        human error, complex to protect SW systems fully                        |                                     SCE framework creation                                     |                                 Experiments to validate the feasibility of ChaosXploit in terms of auditing the security of cloud-managed services, i.e., Amazon buckets.                                  |                                                                                                                            A knowledge database including a set of attack trees and a hypothesis generator.                                                                                                                            |                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        Please refer to Figure 1 in the paper for the architecture to understand the different components and Figure 2 to understand the behaviour using a flow diagram of the execution of a SCE experiment                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        |                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     nan                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     |                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              Evaluating the security of AWS S3 service. It considers the possible configurations and whether they permit establishing a connection, whether they are public or private buckets, or whether they permit getting the configured Access Control Lists (ACLs) which allow managing the access to the buckets and their objects.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               |                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   No specific metrics were used. Only qualitative measures for access control and permissions_x000D_                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   |                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           No particular results. The evaluation was mainly conducted to validate the feasibility of the approach, and I believe that they have demonstrated that._x000D_                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           |                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       The framework can complement previous work that aims to integrate attack tree representation in the knowledge base by selecting the optimal reaction to fire against the threat based on specific criteria. There are no cons explicitly mentioned. However, it is stated that there are many aspects that are still under-explored, e.g., the performance which will determine the applicability of the framework._x000D_                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       |          nan           |
|          10.1117/12.2632779           | 2022 |    Systems of Systems     | 1-3 | No  |  S, T, R, I, D   |        Attack trees         |       T1, T4       |       Empirical       |                   lack of methods for testing security of complex SW systems                   |                               Argues for self-healing software.                                |                                               Measures how long it takes for the system to resume functioning after attacks. Measured by CPU and memory use.                                               |                                                                                                                                           A set of attack trees and a hypothesis generator.                                                                                                                                            |                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  Conduct SCE experimetns using a developed test-bed and a set of attack trees. The experiments include the specification of the observable aspects, steady state, and hypothesis.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  |                                                                                                                                                                                       Software: UAV simulator (VUAV), opensource Chaos Toolkit, NavService, NASA World Wind, OpenPLC, ActiveMQ. Hardware: Global Navigation Satellite System (GNSS).                                                                                                                                                                                        |                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                They use our attack trees as the basis for the CE/SCE experiments on the test bed to evalaute its performance.  These experiments include terminating ActiveMQ , ActiveMQ single queue multi-message flooding, ActiveMQ multi-queue single message flooding, terminating WorldWind, and injecting corrupted NavService. For the first three experiments, they run each experiment (using single virtual machine) for 15 minutes, then they switch to the second, and third respectively. They run the fourth and fifth experiment separately (among two virtual machines) due the requirement of NavService and WorldWind. They evaluate the performance of testbed by measuring the CPU load and RAM Usage of the system.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 |                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     Quantitatite: CPU load and Memory usage of the system._x000D_                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      |                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  CPU Load: average between 0 and 30%.  Memroy: between 5-8 GB on average. _x000D_                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  |                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   SCE useful; selection of performance metrics challenging; _x000D_                                 