|     10.1109/SRDS53918.2021.00014      | 2021 |    Internet of Things     | 4-6 | No  |  S, T, R, I, D   |             NA              |         T5         |       Empirical       |                  SW systems are difficult to secure against fault injections                   |                        IoT, CE tool creation for fault analysis/testing                        |                                Analysing faults/results resulting from fault injection (pre-defined fault model) in a binary, with the goal of identifying vulnerabilities.                                |                                                                                                                        Path to a compiled binary file and specify the architecture the binary was compiled for.                                                                                                                        |                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     automatically injects faults into the binary and collects statistics on the impact of each fault type on software security and stability.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      |                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             Chaos Duck supports both x86 and ARM architectures                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              |                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          They use 5 implementations of PRESENT (which is a block cipher) to perform the evaluation. Mainly looking for data leakage. They test on hardend and non-hardend binaries. Basically they measure the total number of faulted binaries for baseline and hardened versions and collect statistics on fault types and their success rate.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          |                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    Quantitative - Fault detection rate and fault tolerance._x000D_                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     |                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        Quantitative - They present the number of faulted binaries that leaked a plaintext or an encryption key in their outputs (stdout or stderr). - They also  measure the percentage of binaries producing inconsistent results._x000D_                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         |                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         Chaos Duck was able to efficiently inject six different fault types ranging from bit flips to branch faults, and then provide a report on detected security vulnerabilities, including sensitive data leaks,