|                                       |      |                           |     |     |                  |                             |                    |                       |                                                                                                |                                                                                                |                                                                                                                                                                                                            |                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        |                                                                                                                                       Several experiments were carried out to determine the response time, failures, and total requests per second for both the proposed and default systems. The experiments were designed to send a specified volume of traffic to the microservices while maintaining identical settings and configurations. The data were collected and analyzed using Locust reports. The following scenarios were considered: without Fault Injection                                                                                                                                        |                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             