|     10.1007/978-3-031-63783-4_18      | 2024 |    Internet of Things     | 1-3 | No  |  S, T, R, I, D   |             NA              |         T5         |       Empirical       |     complex (large number) IoT systems are difficult to secure, lack of IoT testing tools      |                                CE tool creation for IoT testing                                | The proposed tool intends to inject failures into deviceâ€™s applications as well as seeing how the IoT device runs when there is a continuous, elevated CPU usage, or sudden spike/dip in battery voltages. |                                                                                              An IoT system that can be used to inject faults into and measure the outcome. The paper focuses on using the resource-constrained Zephyr OS.                                                                                              |                                                                                                                                                                                                                       The tool is designed to run on the IoT device and comprises of two components. The uChaos Sensor, and the uChaos Console. The sensor is designed to manipulate the measurement values, and the console manages the sensor intermediate layer and introduces failures.                                                                                                                                                                                                                        |                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     nan                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     |                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  A typical IoT device is used to monitor industrial machines, simulating two different scenarios (temperature and vibrations).Faults were injected and the result studied and compared.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   | Quantitative - Temperature and acceleration (vibration) values altered over time, with anomalies introduceed. Quantitative - Battery voltage values altered over time to replicate unexpected power consumption increase. Values were reduced by 10mV every 2 measurements until the microcontroller behaviour was altered. Quantitative - CPU loading by creating a separate thread that at regular intervals does some variable increment operation for 300ms. Ability for the temperature reading to operate correctly during raised CPU usage was measured._x000D_ |                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                Same as metrics section. Simple tables or graphs are presented showing how the system has introduced faults into the IoT system. No analysis of how the IoT device handles the fault injection is evaluated._x000D_                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 |                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          The uChaos tool is able to introduce a number of fault types into IoT devices running Zephyr OS at the perception layer (manipulating the raw data that the IoT device receives from sensors, battery, etc.)_x000D_                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           |          nan           |
